## \[SECT. XLV.—EMPEROR JIM-MU (PART II.—THE CROSS-SWORD SENT DOWN FROM HEAVEN).\]

So when His Augustness Kamu-yamato-ihare-biko made a progress round from
thence, and reached the village of Kumanu, <span
id="fr_917"></span>[1](#fn_913.md) a large bear came out of the
mountain, <span id="fr_918"></span>[2](#fn_914.md) and forthwith
disappeared into it. Then His Augustness Kamu-yamato-ihare-biko suddenly
fainted away, and his august army likewise all fainted and fell
prostrate. At this time Takakurazhi <span
id="fr_919"></span>[3](#fn_915.md) (<span class="small">this is the name of
a person</span>) <span id="fr_920"></span>[4](#fn_916.md) of Kumanu came
bearing one cross-sword <span id="fr_921"></span>[5](#fn_917.md) to the
place where the august-child of the Deity was lying prostrate, and
presented it to him, upon which the august child of the Heavenly Deity
forthwith rose up, and said: "How long I have slept!" So when he
accepted the cross-sword, the savage Deities of the mountains of Kumanu
all spontaneously fell cut down. <span id="fr_922"></span>[6](#fn_918.md)
Then the whole august

<span id="page_165">p. 165</span>

army, that had been bewildered and had fallen prostrate, awoke and rose
up. So the august child of the Heavenly Deity asked him how he had got
the cross-sword. Takakurazhi \[135\] replied, saying: "I was told in a
dream that

the two Deities the Heaven-Shining-Great-Deity <span
id="fr_923"></span>[7](#fn_919.md) and the High Integrating Deity <span
id="fr_924"></span>[8](#fn_920.md) commanded and summoned the
Brave-Awful-Possessing-Male-Deity, <span id="fr_925"></span>[9](#fn_921.md)
and charged him \[thus\]: 'The Central Land of Reed-Plains <span
id="fr_926"></span>[10](#fn_922.md) is painfully uproarious,—it is. <span
id="fr_927"></span>[11](#fn_923.md) Our august children must be ill at
ease. As \[therefore\] the Central Land of Reed-Plains is a land which
thou specially subduedst, thou the Brave-Awful-Possessing-Male-Deity
shalt descend \[thither\].' Then he replied, saying: 'I <span
id="fr_928"></span>[12](#fn_924.md) will not descend \[myself\], but I have
the cross-sword wherewith I specially subdued the land. (<span
class="small">The name by which this sword is called is the Deity
Thrust-Snap; <span id="fr_929"></span>[13](#fn_925.md) another name by
which it is called is the Deity Awful-Snap, <span
id="fr_930"></span>[14](#fn_926.md) and another name for it is the
August-Snap-Spirit, <span id="fr_931"></span>[15](#fn_927.md) This sword
dwells in the temple of the Deity of Isonokami</span>) <span
id="fr_932"></span>[16](#fn_928.md) The manner in which I will send this
sword down will be to perforate the ridge of \[the roof of\]
Takakurazhi's stone-house, <span id="fr_933"></span>[17](#fn_929.md) and
drop it through. (So the Brave-Awful-Possessing-Male-Deity instructed
me, saying: 'I will perforate the ridge of \[the roof of\] thy
store-house, and drop this sword through. <span
id="fr_934"></span>[18](#fn_930).md) So do thou, with the good eyes of
\[136\] morning, <span id="fr_935"></span>[19](#fn_931.md) take it and
present it to the august child of the Heavenly Deity.' So, on my
searching my store-house early next morning in accordance with the
instructions of the dream, there really was a cross-sword there. So I
just present this cross-sword to thee."

